      "body" : "The list returned by <code>Arrays.asList()</code> is <i>NOT</i> unmodifiable, @kocko.  It has a fixed size, but you can change the references to point to entirely different objects like <code>Arrays.asList(...).set(0,new String(&quot;new string&quot;))</code>  This code will work and set the first element of the list to the String object with value &quot;new string&quot;.  And in fact, it writes through to the native array!  Definitely <i>not</i> unmodifiable."
